"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-news-world-raygun-breaking-breakdancing-paris-2024-olympics-b1180003.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google Custom Search\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See our privacy policy for more information.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"News|World  Australian breakdancer Rachael \\\"Raygun\\\" Gunn has apologised after facing backlash for her performance at the recentOlympic Games.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 370, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 241, \"end\": 251, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9998951403456782, \"rank\": 0.00010002608469981713, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 264, \"end\": 271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachael_Ray\", \"score\": 0.9999999999740794, \"rank\": 2.429122336700403e-11, \"text\": \"Rachael\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachael_Ray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachael_Ray\"}, {\"begin\": 273, \"end\": 279, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3220763122118216e-31, \"text\": \"Raygun\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 37-year-old became an internet sensation when she competed at the Paris Games in breakdancing, one of four newly introduced sports.\", \"from\": 372, \"to\": 507, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gunn was knocked out of the round-robin stage of the B-girls (break-girls) competition with zero points - but her unusual moves captured the world's attention.\", \"from\": 509, \"to\": 668, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These included hopping around like a kangaroo, grabbing her chin, and flapping around on stage in front of the judges as she went head-to-head with another B-girl.\", \"from\": 670, \"to\": 833, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, her unorthodox performance attracted a mixture of praise and ridicule.\", \"from\": 835, \"to\": 914, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She spoke to Network Ten'sThe Projectabout the response she had received.\", \"from\": 916, \"to\": 989, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It is really sad to hear those criticisms,\\\" the lecturer in the Department of Media, Communications, Creative Arts, Language and Literature at Macquarie University Faculty of Arts told host Waleed Aly.\", \"from\": 991, \"to\": 1193, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1182, \"end\": 1192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Waleed_Aly\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Waleed Aly\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Waleed_Aly\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Waleed_Aly\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"And I am very sorry for the backlash that the community has experienced, but I can not control how people react.\\\"\", \"from\": 1195, \"to\": 1309, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gunn also explained that having people chase her left her in a \\\"state of panic\\\".\", \"from\": 1311, \"to\": 1391, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But, when asked if she was Australia's best female breakdancer, she said: \\\"I think my record speaks to that.\\\"\", \"from\": 1393, \"to\": 1502, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1420, \"end\": 1429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9976028598651694, \"rank\": 0.0019625141431799634, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She previously addressed her evocative performance on social media.\", \"from\": 1504, \"to\": 1571, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She said in August: \\\"I just want to start by thanking all the people who have supported me.\", \"from\": 1573, \"to\": 1664, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I really appreciate the positivity, and I am glad I was able to bring some joy into your lives.\", \"from\": 1665, \"to\": 1760, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's what I hoped.\", \"from\": 1762, \"to\": 1783, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I did not realise that that would also open the door to so much hate, which has, frankly, been pretty devastating.\\\"\", \"from\": 1784, \"to\": 1899, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Well, I went out there and I had fun.\", \"from\": 1901, \"to\": 1939, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I did take it very seriously.\", \"from\": 1940, \"to\": 1969, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I worked my butt off preparing for theOlympics, and I gave my all,\\\" she added.\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 2048, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Breakdancing originated as a counterculture dance form from the US and is associated with the hip-hop community.\", \"from\": 2050, \"to\": 2162, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2114, \"end\": 2116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9986727477969354, \"rank\": 0.0013236285176688402, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is competitively known as breaking and joined skateboarding,\\u00a0sport climbing, and surfing\\u00a0in making its debut at the 2024 Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 2164, \"to\": 2302, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, some critics questioned breaking's role as an Olympic sport following Gunn's performance.\", \"from\": 2304, \"to\": 2402, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Another standout moment from the breaking competition was the disqualification of Afghan athlete Manizha Talash, who wore a cape that said \\\"free Afghan women\\\".\", \"from\": 2404, \"to\": 2563, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2486, \"end\": 2492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghans\", \"score\": 0.9995421138790657, \"rank\": 0.0004580538508511425, \"text\": \"Afghan\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghans\"}, {\"begin\": 2501, \"end\": 2508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manizha\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Manizha\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manizha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manizha\"}, {\"begin\": 2509, \"end\": 2515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Talash_(1969_film)\", \"score\": 0.858682698055531, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Talash\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q11424\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Talash_(1969_film)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Talash_(1969_film)\"}, {\"begin\": 2549, \"end\": 2555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghans\", \"score\": 0.9995421138790657, \"rank\": 0.0004580538508511425, \"text\": \"Afghan\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The refugee Olympian, who defied most odds to secure her spot at the Games, lost her position because she displayed a 'political' message during the games.\", \"from\": 2565, \"to\": 2720, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2577, \"end\": 2585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.99999996731458, \"rank\": 3.268494069547776e-08, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Breaking will not appear as a sport at the next Olympic Games in Los Angeles in 2028.\", \"from\": 2722, \"to\": 2807, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2787, \"end\": 2798, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999949978, \"rank\": 3.4860537521231144e-12, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While some people on the internet suggested that Raygun may have caused this,Esquirereported that local organisers choose Olympic sports much earlier.\", \"from\": 2809, \"to\": 2959, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2858, \"end\": 2864, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3220763122118216e-31, \"text\": \"Raygun\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Raygun!\", \"from\": 2961, \"to\": 2968, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Muffins!\", \"from\": 2969, \"to\": 2977, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pole vault fails!\", \"from\": 2978, \"to\": 2995, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The viral moments from Paris 2024 so far  Viral breakdancer Raygun speaks out on 'devastating hate' after Olympics performance  Which sports are in and out of LA 2028 Olympics?\", \"from\": 2996, \"to\": 3172, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3019, \"end\": 3029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.063265789